{
  "name": "Succession",
  "framework": "crt",
  "direction": "BT",
  "showGrid": true,
  "snapToGrid": false,
  "edgeRoutingMode": "fixed",
  "version": 3,
  "createdAt": "2026-04-01T04:28:14.293Z",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "c4ddfce8-54de-4cca-80c3-64f9e5fed140",
      "label": "There is currently no Roy family member serving as the CEO of the company.",
      "tags": [
        "ude"
      ],
      "isUDE": true,
      "notes": "Matsson names Tom Wambsgans U.S. CEO (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nOn the pier after the vote, Kendall, defeated: \"It’s done. It’s over. We’re bullshit. We always were.\"",
      "x": 992,
      "y": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "3b4e0dd5-e601-4560-8592-4daeb70e76c6",
      "label": "The board has voted to approve the sale of the company to GoJo.",
      "notes": "Board vote passes 7–6 accepting GoJo deal (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nKarl, gavel in hand: \"Ladies and gentlemen, congratulations. The motion passes and the resolution is adopted.\"",
      "x": 994,
      "y": 208
    },
    {
      "id": "3c7e442f-7fcc-40a9-92ed-e025bf04fd03",
      "label": "Shiv voted in favor of the company's sale during the meeting.",
      "notes": "Shiv casts the decisive \"yes\" in boardroom vote (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nShiv whispers to Kendall, voice breaking: \"I’m sorry, I just… I can’t. I’m sorry.\"",
      "x": 714,
      "y": 404
    },
    {
      "id": "f1c90017-e365-4f02-a713-6c34e321916e",
      "label": "There is ongoing distrust and rivalry among the siblings.",
      "notes": "Roman: \"We’re broken debris, floating after Dad… pathetic, messy little fucking nothings.\" (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nSibling alliances have shifted constantly—Pierce coup vs. GoJo (S3E09 \"All the Bells Say\").",
      "x": 953,
      "y": 772
    },
    {
      "id": "acbf0a22-2790-44a2-b62d-b0533a0ad61a",
      "label": "Logan did not establish a clear succession plan for the company.",
      "notes": "Logan tears up succession papers on 80th birthday (S1E01 \"Celebration\").\nLater, furious, Logan growls: \"Make your own fucking pile. I’m not giving you an inch unless you earn it.\" (S3E09 \"All the Bells Say\").",
      "x": 1364,
      "y": 944
    },
    {
      "id": "eff7a9cf-a7a1-4e83-aa95-23581786e63a",
      "label": "The truth about Kendall's involvement in the waiter’s death remains concealed.",
      "notes": "Kendall kills waiter Andrew Dodds in car accident (S1E10 \"Nobody Is Ever Missing\").\nShiv hisses to Kendall in the bathroom: \"You killed someone, Ken. A waiter. Dad covered it up. So maybe don’t act like the moral high ground is yours.\" (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").",
      "x": 1084,
      "y": 944
    },
    {
      "id": "a9855b0a-8355-4a49-ac05-36e3905f6e96",
      "label": "GoJo has made a premium bid to acquire the company.",
      "notes": "Matsson ups bid to $192/share, 40% premium (S4E09 \"Church and State\").\nGerri: \"It’s a good number.\" (S4E09).",
      "x": 994,
      "y": 416
    },
    {
      "id": "460a1e9a-e889-4dc4-9dca-efba0ac7d1b0",
      "label": "Scandals at Waystar are continuing to escalate.",
      "notes": "NY Mag exposé on Cruises abuses surfaces (S2E01 \"The Summer Palace\").\nSenate hearings hammer Waystar over cover-up (S2E09 \"DC\").",
      "x": 1234,
      "y": 600
    },
    {
      "id": "71acd8f7-f52d-4e69-9a8e-7f9d39221e3b",
      "label": "Logan employed manipulative parenting techniques with his children.",
      "notes": "Logan bellows across the newsroom floor: \"I love you, but you are not serious people. You are unserious fucking children, all of you!\" (S4E02 \"Rehearsal\").\nLogan divides kids into rival softball teams (S1E01 \"Celebration\").",
      "x": 265,
      "y": 1492
    },
    {
      "id": "5a7c6ec1-2fa8-424a-9cb6-488dc6fbd846",
      "label": "Logan's unexpected death has impacted the company's succession plans.",
      "notes": "The flight captain, voice trembling, tells Tom on the sat-phone: \"Mr. Wambsgans, I’m sorry… he’s gone. Mr. Roy never regained consciousness.\" (S4E03 \"Connor’s Wedding\").\nIn-flight death forces immediate succession scramble.",
      "x": 288,
      "y": 400
    },
    {
      "id": "d241b1dd-0b39-428e-a77d-d9fdfc88876e",
      "label": "Matsson is seeking a pliable figurehead to lead the company.",
      "notes": "Matsson smirks to Shiv at the party: \"I kinda like him, you know? He’s flexible, got a decent vibe, won’t make it weird—unlike certain people who share the company name.\" (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nMatsson tells Shiv a Roy CEO would look \"messy\" (S4E09 \"Church and State\").",
      "x": 295,
      "y": 888
    },
    {
      "id": "19b10185-f655-4baa-9806-6df270a34b68",
      "label": "The company is facing significant regulatory and political risks.",
      "notes": "Hugo whispers urgently to Kendall: \"The DOJ is thinking RICO, alright? Like, full-fat racketeering charges. Real jail time.\" (S3E08 \"Chiantishire\").\nMencken election uncertainty spooks investors (S4E08 \"America Decides\").",
      "x": 1274,
      "y": 404
    },
    {
      "id": "e1b336a8-5075-4f1a-91ae-ca6673d9118b",
      "label": "Roman is involved in a scandal due to inappropriate pictures.",
      "notes": "Shiv reminds Roman in the limo: \"You sent the dick-pic, Rome. To Gerri. On a company phone. That’s a sexual-harassment time-bomb.\" (S3E09 \"All the Bells Say\").\nLeak threat pushes Gerri to advise Roman step back.",
      "x": 823,
      "y": 944
    },
    {
      "id": "1a81bef9-cfb1-44df-b57e-e10745d170f1",
      "label": "Kendall continues to struggle with ongoing addiction issues.",
      "notes": "Kendall, high and dripping, yells at Stewy by the pool: \"I’m better than you! I’m a fucking killer! I’m a good guy who does bad things. I’m the real thing, man!\" (S3E08 \"Chiantishire\").\nRelapse rumors raise boardroom credibility concerns.",
      "x": 543,
      "y": 944
    },
    {
      "id": "9b847187-f684-4f35-bff8-fde6e5fd3be8",
      "label": "Shiv does not hold a strong or consistent track record.",
      "notes": "Matsson teases Shiv on the balcony: \"Zero numbers on the board, Shiv. Nothing. Nada. You’re pitching vaporware with a smile.\" (S4E10 \"With Open Eyes\").\nShiv quit politics after failed Gil Eavis campaign (S2E04 \"Safe Room\").",
      "x": 23,
      "y": 772
    },
    {
      "id": "79185721-3c28-4fa2-9c9f-cce87b845706",
      "label": "Shiv has personal ambitions tied to the sale.",
      "x": 297,
      "y": 524
    },
    {
      "id": "b5338255-a247-4355-b3ae-c5397f0f73ad",
      "label": "Matsson offers Shiv the U.S. CEO role as a backroom deal.",
      "notes": "Matsson privately tells Shiv she could run U.S. operations post-acquisition (S4E09 \"Church and State\"). This is the carrot that flips her from blocking the deal to enabling it.",
      "x": 305,
      "y": 730
    },
    {
      "id": "0c41448d-3187-4de6-9609-5fe2f3ebf78f",
      "label": "The Shiv-Tom marriage has broken down irreparably.",
      "notes": "Shiv tells Tom: \"We're done, Tom. I think we both know that.\" (S4E07 \"Tailgate Party\"). Their separation has been building since Tom chose Logan over Shiv in S3E09.",
      "x": 263,
      "y": 1336
    },
    {
      "id": "f8e1db46-7964-41b7-99c0-cd6902b30d3d",
      "label": "Tom secretly feeds information to Matsson and allies with him.",
      "notes": "Tom's betrayal of the Roys to Logan (S3E09) establishes his pattern of self-preservation. By S4, Tom is Matsson's inside channel, positioning himself as useful and pliable.",
      "x": 263,
      "y": 1140
    },
    {
      "id": "83bc4a53-ae22-4528-bf7e-b355d69f7772",
      "label": "Kendall cannot credibly lead the company.",
      "notes": "Between addiction, the waiter cover-up, erratic behavior, and failed bids for control, Kendall's CEO candidacy is fatally compromised in the eyes of the board and his own siblings.",
      "x": 738,
      "y": 600
    }
  ],
